The paper also involves direct sum theorems, which are related to distributed computing and communication complexity, making cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves information theory, as it deals with error probabilities and communication complexity, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category.
